Hisense is celebrating the launch of its Infinity H60 smartphones in South Africa by giving you the chance to win exciting weekly prizes. The Infinity H60 range signals a big step forward for Hisense’s smartphone division and comprises three options: the H60 5G, H60 Zoom, and H60 Lite. The Hisense H60 5G is the top-of-the-range Infinity smartphone and supports next-generation 5G technology that provides much faster Internet speeds. It is powered by an impressive 8GB RAM and an octa-core processor. Additionally, it boasts a powerful quad-lens camera system that includes an all-new 108MP lens – enhanced by an innovative high-resolution algorithm. The Infinity H60 5G also comes with 128GB storage and a 4,200mAh battery that offers 30W quick charging. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-441654" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H601.png" alt="" width="640" height="350" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H601.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H601-600x328.png 600w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The Hisense H60 Zoom brings high-end photography capabilities to more South Africans. It packs a quad-lens camera that can capture stunning 108MP photos for best-in-class snaps. The Zoom also packs an impressive 6GB RAM and offers a 6.78-inch FHD+ O-Infinity display to give a truly premium experience. All of this is powered by a powerful 5,000mAh battery that supports 18W quick charge technology. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-441656" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H602.png" alt="" width="640" height="350" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H602.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H602-600x328.png 600w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Hisense has also unveiled the Infinity H60 Lite, packed with impressive features at an affordable price. Standout features include 4GB RAM, 128GB storage, a 5,150mAh battery with 15W quick charge, and a quad-lens rear camera system that includes a 48MP primary lens. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-441658" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H603.png" alt="" width="640" height="350" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H603.png 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Hisense-H603-600x328.png 600w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> To celebrate the launch of these Hisense Infinity H60 smartphones, Hisense is running a campaign focused on helping fans to “reimagine their hustle.” This campaign will take you on an exciting treasure hunt that will simultaneously provide interesting information about Hisense Mobile and its Infinity H60 smartphones, while giving you the chance to win great prizes. The search will begin in Sebenza Taxis, and commuters will be asked to unlock a series of fun quests along this route – including taking a picture of a Hisense billboard, and following Hisense on social media. Those who complete these tasks will be entered into a raffle where they will stand a chance to win a range of weekly prizes. Keep an eye out for other exciting initiatives like this one in the coming weeks as Hisense Mobile promotes its Infinity H60 smartphone range. Click here to view Hisense Mobile South Africa’s full range of smartphones. Specifications for the new Hisense smartphones are listed below.